entry.summary:
  A sketch of the affine quantum gravity program illustrates a different
perspective on several difficult issues of principle: metric positivity;
quantum anomalies; and nonrenormalizability.

  If the cosmological constant $\Lambda $ can not be neglected, we will show in
this short report, that graviton should have a rest mass $m_g=\sqrt{2\Lambda
}=\sqrt{2\Lambda}\hbar c^{-1}$ different from zero.
